Note:
Runa Scientific Computing: Optimization Solvers (Compatibility Layer)

This is a compatibility wrapper that imports from the unified math optimization engine.
All functionality has been moved to math/engine/optimization for better architecture.
:End Note

Import "math/engine/optimization/solvers" as SolverEngine

Note: Re-export solver functions
Process called "bfgs_solver" that takes func as Any and x0 as Any and gradient as Any returns Any:
    Return SolverEngine.bfgs_solver with func as func and x0 as x0 and gradient as gradient

Process called "lbfgs_solver" that takes func as Any and x0 as Any and gradient as Any returns Any:
    Return SolverEngine.lbfgs_solver with func as func and x0 as x0 and gradient as gradient

Process called "newton_solver" that takes func as Any and x0 as Any and gradient as Any and hessian as Any returns Any:
    Return SolverEngine.newton_solver with func as func and x0 as x0 and gradient as gradient and hessian as hessian

Process called "conjugate_gradient_solver" that takes func as Any and x0 as Any and gradient as Any returns Any:
    Return SolverEngine.conjugate_gradient_solver with func as func and x0 as x0 and gradient as gradient

Process called "trust_region_solver" that takes func as Any and x0 as Any and gradient as Any returns Any:
    Return SolverEngine.trust_region_solver with func as func and x0 as x0 and gradient as gradient

Process called "interior_point_solver" that takes func as Any and x0 as Any and constraints as Any returns Any:
    Return SolverEngine.interior_point_solver with func as func and x0 as x0 and constraints as constraints

Process called "sqp_solver" that takes func as Any and x0 as Any and constraints as Any returns Any:
    Return SolverEngine.sqp_solver with func as func and x0 as x0 and constraints as constraints